io.smudgr.app.project.util

Class PropertyMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smudgr.app.project.util.PropertyMap

  • public class PropertyMap
extends java.lang.Object
    The PropertyMap class can be used to store hierarchical DOM-style data.

    Property maps have attributes and value pairs, as well as nested child maps.

    Property maps can be serialized into a JSON-ready structure with ApiMessage.normalize(PropertyMap) or persisted as XML using the ProjectSaver

    Nested property maps are passed recursively through the Project structure and are used to persist and load project data.

      • PropertyMap

        public PropertyMap(ProjectItem item)
        Create a property map with the given ProjectItem.

        This immediately calls ProjectItem.save(PropertyMap).

        This will set the map tag to ReflectableType.getTypeCategoryIdentifier() and the type attribute to ReflectableType.getTypeIdentifier().

        If the given element has a project ID, the id attribute is set to Project.getId(ProjectItem)

        Parameters:
        item - ProjectItem
        See Also:
        ProjectItem.save(PropertyMap)
